#Rwanda shunned ethnic politics, #Rwandans are a united people, determined all together to transform their country regardless of their tribal or political affiliations.

When President #Kagame took over the country's leadership, he created a conducive environment for the return of refugees. Over 200,000 refugees returned to the government, the majority coming from the former #Zaire now #DRC.

In December 2017, the #UNHCR’s cessation clause ending the refugee status for #Rwandans came into effect. Those who claim to be refuge are convicted criminals and individuals with pending cases in courts of law who fled accountability.

It’s in #DRC where new leadership forces people to flee their own country. #Tshisekedi’s divisive regime deprived Congolese Tutsis of their fundamental rights of existence, nationality, and land. They were forced to flee to #Rwanda and #Uganda.

#Congolese army took part in the #GenocideAgainstTutsis when #Zaire’s dictator Mobutu deployed them to reinforce #Habyarimana’s genocidal forces. History never forgets.

#FDLR was created by defeated genocidal forces and the #Congolese regime authorities who welcomed them into the country and offered a safe haven for the murderers to reorganize and return to Rwanda for their unfinished business. They still have plans to exterminate all Tutsis.

#Tshisekedi must neutralize #FDLR and repatriate its members to #Rwanda to pave the way for peace in the #EasternDRC and stability in the region.

#Tshisekedi must negotiate with #M23/#AFC to end the inter-#Congolese crisis.

