In 1990, the Uganda Army, posing as the #RPF, invaded #Rwanda. Despite clear evidence of Uganda's involvement, the #UN Security Council didn't act, attributing it to Rwandans returning home. After more proof, Rwanda's repeated calls to the OAU for sanctions were also ignored, leading to a devastating war and war crimes by the RPF, climaxing in the 1994 Rwandan Genocide that destabilised the region. Recently, #DRC President #Tshisekedi's similar plea to the UN regarding Rwanda and the #M23 was rejected. We can't solely rely on external forces to resolve our crises, but we remain hopeful that the African Union will learn from its past mistakes and fully support the #SADC operation in eastern DRC to prevent another regional disaster.

