URGENT BREAKING NEWS!!! Mustafa Abdulfatahu who is #Bicahaga son is missing, thanks to the #Rwandagov which is dividing & destroying families at a large scale (see our previous newsletter & picture below). @EU_Commission @POTUS @SecBlinken @SamanthaJPower @Europarl_EN @UNICEF 

BACKGROUND: The Rwanda government wanted to kill Bicahaga @AmatekaT47424 following of his freedom of expression & YouTube channel. Bicahaga then fled to another country. Following his flight, the government began to persecute the family. They imprisoned Bicahaga's wife, a mother of 4 children. They did not care that this mother is leaving behind 4 minor children. They also jailed the children but released them after a few weeks. 

#Rwandagov took the children out of their own home in #Kigali to a poor aunt who lives in a remote area as you can see on the pictures. The children were not close to this aunt but still they were forced to leave school, their goods and beautiful home in Kigali. The government gave orders that the children are not allowed to leave this poor village where these children barely know anyone. They forbade the children also to go to the mosque nor receive any money or any donation. 

#Rwandagov also forbade the children to talk to their father at their free will. The children are allowed to talk to their father only twice a month! 

CHILDREN EDUCATION: Because of your advocacy (keep it at every level, with every strength within you), the #Rwandagov sent social workers to the remote area. The children were not going to school and the poor aunt could not put them all in school. So the government gave order to divide the children among the relatives. The children are not close to these relatives and they did not ask their consent but the families began to divide them among themselves. 

On September 6, the older son by the name of Mustafa Abdulfatahu (whose picture below) could not bear the stress and the hunger in this remote village and he run away to go find means of survival. At the moment we write this, Mustafa was seen on his way to Kigali but he is broke and had no money on himself. The driver who had accepted to give him a ride left him half the way after finding that he did not have money on himself.

For the sake of humanity, dear advocates, wherever you are, please advocate for #Bicahaga family. They are 1 in thousands suffering this kind of treatment inside #Rwanda. Let the government of Rwanda know that should anything happen to Mustafa, they will be held responsible. @EmmanuelMacron @hrw @AmnestyEARO
